section.p:
We have defined the sine and cosine in terms of the ordered pairs a distance s from \left(1,0 \right) along the path defined by the unit circle,

        \cos\left(s \right)=  \amp \text{ the } x-\text{coordinate of the point}
        \sin\left(s \right)=  \amp \text{ the } y-\text{coordinate of the point}

    Picturing the unit circle in our mind’s eye, remembering that the multiples of \pi and \frac{\pi}{2} designate the zeros and the maximum and minimum values for sine and cosine will make it easier to sketch the graphs of these important functions.
